<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="552" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1108,1565]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1180,1205]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Discussion.</emphasis>
The species was described based on an unspecified number of females from 
<collectingCountry box="[1289,1375,1180,1205]" name="Bolivia" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. The depository of its 
<typeStatus box="[343,391,1216,1240]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">type</typeStatus>
material has remained unknown so far. A single female belonging to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Stal, 1862" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Dystus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1301,1377,1217,1240]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Dystus</emphasis>
Stål, 
<number box="[151,207,1252,1277]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" value="1862.0">1862</number>
</taxonomicName>
was found among unidentified scutellerids in 
<collectionCode box="[729,795,1252,1276]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">SDEI</collectionCode>
. As it perfectly fits the original description of 
<taxonomicName authority="Stål, 1862" authorityName="Stål" authorityYear="1862" box="[1316,1435,1252,1276]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Dystus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis box="[1316,1435,1252,1276]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">D. villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it is from the 
<typeStatus box="[348,396,1288,1312]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">type</typeStatus>
locality, there is no doubt that it is a 
<typeStatus box="[809,896,1288,1312]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">syntype</typeStatus>
and it is therefore designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[1303,1406,1287,1312]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Stål, 1862" authorityName="Stål" authorityYear="1862" box="[151,270,1324,1348]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Dystus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis box="[151,270,1324,1348]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">D. villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1108,1565]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">
The species was synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authority="Stal, 1862" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[603,870,1359,1384]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Dystus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puberulus">
<emphasis box="[603,750,1360,1384]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">D. puberulus</emphasis>
Stål, 
<number box="[814,870,1359,1384]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" value="1862.0">1862</number>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schouteden" box="[913,1129,1359,1384]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" refString="Schouteden, H. (1904) Heteroptera, fam. Pentatomidae, subfam. Scutellerinae. In: Wytsman, P. (Ed.), Genera Insectorum, 24, 1 - 98, pls. 1 - 5." type="journal article" year="1904">
Schouteden (
<number box="[1060,1121,1360,1384]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" value="1904.0">1904</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
; we confirm the synonymy of the two species. The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Stål, 1862" authorityName="Stål" authorityYear="1862" box="[501,577,1397,1420]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Dystus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[501,577,1397,1420]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Dystus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently monotypic; a photo of the only included species was given by Eger 
<emphasis box="[214,274,1432,1456]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[292,353,1431,1456]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" value="2015.0">2015</number>
), ink drawings and descriptions of the adult and all preimaginal stages as well as the genital capsule and parameres of the male were provided by Cervantes 
<bibRefCitation author="Peredo" box="[872,1035,1468,1493]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" refString="Cervantes-Peredo, L. (2004) Dystus puberulus Stal (Heteroptera: Scutelleridae) a shield bug associated with figs in Mexico. Florida Entomologist, 87 (4), 528 - 532. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1653 / 0015 - 4040 (2004) 087 [0528: DPSHSA] 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2004">
Peredo (
<number box="[966,1028,1468,1492]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. The latter work also documents its host plant and life cycle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1108,1565]" box="[199,1048,1540,1565]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,380,1540,1565]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Current status.</emphasis>
Junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Stal, 1862" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1862" box="[725,1044,1540,1565]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Dystus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puberulus">
<emphasis box="[725,920,1540,1564]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="552">Dystus puberulus</emphasis>
Stål, 
<number box="[984,1044,1540,1565]" pageId="1" pageNumber="552" value="1862.0">1862</number>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
